      "content": "i hear you, but it feels like the school's side is being framed as the only \"logical\" one. you said it's a \"necessary step\" but then said the parents just want to \"protect\" kids. doesn't that make the school's position sound like the objective truth and the parents just sound like they're being defensive or reacting emotionally? why is the school's approach considered the standard or the \"correct\" way to do things?",
